\cf9 ## 3.2 Figma: Visual Design & Developer Handoff\
\
**Purpose:** Single source of truth for visual design, design systems, and developer specifications.\
\
### Key Integration Points\
\
| Feature | Implementation | Benefit |\
|:--------|:---------------|:--------|\
| **Dev Mode** | Enable for all design files | Developers access specs, CSS, assets without leaving Figma [^15^] |\
| **Design Tokens** | Sync variables with code repository | Colors, typography, spacing consistent across design and code |\
| **Azure DevOps Plugin** | One-click work item creation from components | Design context automatically attached to backlog items [^13^] |\
| **VS Code Extension** | Developers inspect designs in IDE | Eliminates context switching; code suggestions based on designs [^17^] |\
| **Section Statuses** | Mark frames as "Ready for Dev" | Clear handoff signals; prevents premature implementation [^19^] |\
\
### Figma Workflow in Scrum\
\
1. **Sprint Planning:** Designers mark stories as "Ready for Dev" in Figma; developers review Dev Mode specs\
2. **Daily Standup:** Developers reference Figma links for implementation questions; designers annotate clarifications\
3. **Sprint Review:** Compare implemented features against Figma prototypes; capture deviations as new stories\
4. **Backlog Refinement:** Use Figma comments to discuss technical feasibility before sizing\
\
## 3.3 Relume: Rapid Structure & Wireframing\
\
**Purpose:** AI-powered sitemap and wireframe generation to accelerate early-stage planning and civic engagement prototyping.\
\
### Key Integration Points\
\
| Feature | Implementation | Benefit |\
|:--------|:---------------|:--------|\
| **AI Sitemap Generator** | Input ministry service descriptions; generate page structures | Rapidly prototype civic engagement user journeys [^18^] |\
| **Wireframe Export** | Export low-fidelity wireframes to Figma | Designers start from structured foundation, not blank canvas [^24^] |\
| **Style Guide Builder** | Define color palettes, typography, UI elements | Consistent design system across all ministry digital services [^25^] |\
| **Figma Library Plugin** | 1,000+ pre-built components with mobile variants | Accelerate responsive design for civic engagement platforms [^27^] |\
| **Webflow Export** | Direct export to Webflow for rapid prototyping | Validate concepts with stakeholders before engineering investment [^24^] |\
\
### Relume Workflow in Big Picture Planning\
\
1. **Rock Definition:** Use Relume AI to generate sitemaps for new civic engagement initiatives; validate scope with stakeholders\
2. **Epic Decomposition:** Convert sitemaps to wireframes; identify cross-page dependencies and shared components\
3. **Design Refinement:** Import wireframes to Figma; apply ministry design system; customize for specific service needs\
4. **Story Creation:** Component-based stories derived from Relume library elements; consistent sizing and acceptance criteria\
\
## 3.4 CodeSpring: Design-to-Code Automation\
\
**Purpose:** Bridge the final gap between approved designs and production-ready code, automating the translation of design specifications into development tasks and initial code scaffolding.\
\
### Key Integration Points\
\
| Feature | Implementation | Benefit |\
|:--------|:---------------|:--------|\
| **Visual Knowledge Base** | Ingests repository structure; maps to design components | Code lands in correct architectural locations [^20^] |\
| **PRD Generation** | Auto-generates Product Requirements Documents from designs | Reduces documentation overhead; ensures specification completeness |\
| **MCP Integration** | Sends specifications to Cursor/Claude with exact paths | AI-assisted coding with proper context and file locations [^20^] |\
| **Drift Prevention** | Re-ingests commits to update knowledge base | Design system and code remain synchronized |\
| **Task Automation** | Creates development tasks linked to design components | Traceability from design decision to code implementation |\
\
### CodeSpring Workflow in Continuous Delivery\
\
1. **Design Approval:** Finalized Figma components marked "Ready for Dev" trigger CodeSpring analysis\
2. **Specification Generation:** CodeSpring generates PRDs with component architecture, props, and file paths\
3. **Backlog Integration:** Development tasks auto-created in Azure DevOps with Figma links and CodeSpring specs\
4. **Development:** Developers use Cursor/Claude with MCP to implement against specifications\
5. **Synchronization:** Commits re-ingested to CodeSpring; design system drift flagged for remediation\
\
