# 4. Concerns & Risk Mitigation\
\
## 4.1 Current Infrastructure Concerns\
\
| Concern | Severity | Mitigation Strategy | Owner |\
|:--------|:---------|:--------------------|:------|\
| **Complexity Overhead** | Medium | Start simple; add ceremony only when friction emerges; favor working software over comprehensive documentation | Scrum Master Community |\
| **Resistance to Change** | High | Invest in practical training (not certification mills); establish change champions from respected practitioners | Change Management |\
| **Tooling Fragmentation** | Medium | Consolidate on ministry-standard toolchain; integrate existing tools before adding new ones | Platform Team |\
| **Top-Down vs. Team Autonomy** | Medium | Big Picture provides context, not control; teams own "how"; leadership owns "what" and "why" | Leadership |\
| **Skills Gap** | High | Peer coaching program; communities of practice; just-in-time training vs. upfront heavy investment | HR/Training |\
| **Design-Dev Handoff Friction** | Medium | Mandatory Figma Dev Mode usage; CodeSpring integration; design reviews in Sprint Demo | Design Lead |\
\
## 4.2 Operational Risks\
\
### Risk: Planning Fatigue\
- **Description:** Multi-level refinement becomes ceremonial rather than valuable\
- **Mitigation:** Strict timeboxing; focus on dependency resolution and risk identification; use retrospectives to refine format; cancel if no value\
\
### Risk: "Water-Scrum" Anti-Pattern\
- **Description:** Big Picture planning reintroduces waterfall tendencies through excessive upfront analysis\
- **Mitigation:** Emphasize emergence over prediction; maintain iterative delivery at team level; inspect and adapt planning practices quarterly\
\
### Risk: Dependency Gridlock\
- **Description:** Cross-team dependencies block flow despite planning\
- **Mitigation:** Visual dependency boards; daily cross-team sync; architectural investment to decouple systems; swarm blocked items\
\
### Risk: Design Tool Adoption\
- **Description:** Teams revert to old design tools or manual handoff processes\
- **Mitigation:** Embed Figma/Relume/CodeSpring in Definition of Done; measure design-to-code lead time; celebrate reduced handoff time wins\
\
