# 6. Implementation Roadmap\
\
## 6.1 90-Day Quick Wins\
\
### Month 1: Foundation\
- [ ] Establish ministry Scrum community with team representatives\
- [ ] Conduct initial Big Picture planning session (strategic rocks identification)\
- [ ] Implement team-level Scrum with Definition of Done including deployment\
- [ ] Deploy visual backlog hierarchy (physical or digital) in team spaces\
- [ ] **Install Figma Dev Mode licenses; configure Azure DevOps plugin** [^19^]\
- [ ] **Set up Relume accounts for design team; import ministry design system** [^27^]\
\
### Month 2: Integration\
- [ ] Launch Cross-Team Sync for dependency management\
- [ ] Implement automated deployment pipeline with blue-green capability\
- [ ] Establish Program Refinement sessions (weekly epic decomposition)\
- [ ] Begin Strategic Refinement (monthly rock definition)\
- [ ] **Integrate CodeSpring with primary repositories; configure MCP for Cursor/Claude** [^20^]\
- [ ] **First design-to-code sprint using full tool chain (Relume \uc0\u8594  Figma \u8594  CodeSpring \u8594  Azure DevOps)**\
\
### Month 3: Optimization\
- [ ] First integrated Sprint Review demonstrating cross-team delivery\
- [ ] Conduct initial retrospective on planning practices\
- [ ] Measure baseline flow metrics (lead time, deployment frequency)\
- [ ] Plan next quarter based on learnings\
- [ ] **Measure design-to-code lead time; optimize handoff bottlenecks**\
- [ ] **Establish design system governance cadence**\
\
