\
# 7. Conclusion & Next Steps\
\
The Ministry's DevOps deployment has established the technical foundation for continuous delivery. The integration of **Big Picture Planning** with our **hybrid Scrum approach** will weave continuous delivery into the organizational fiber\'97not through framework prescription, but through practical, scaled application of core agile principles.\
\
The addition of **Figma, Relume, and CodeSpring** to our toolchain closes the critical design-to-development gap, enabling rapid prototyping of civic engagement solutions while maintaining production-quality output. This integrated workflow ensures that what gets designed is what gets built, with full traceability from ministry strategy to deployed service.\
\
## Immediate Actions Required\
\
| Priority | Action | Timeline | Owner |\
|:---------|:-------|:---------|:------|\
| 1 | **Leadership Alignment:** Executive briefing on Big Picture Planning and hybrid Scrum scaling | Week 1 | Change Lead |\
| 2 | **Community Launch:** Charter ministry Scrum community with identified representatives | Week 2 | Scrum Master Community |\
| 3 | **Training Focus:** Practical Scrum workshops; multi-level refinement training; just-in-time coaching | Weeks 2-4 | HR/Training |\
| 4 | **First Big Picture Session:** Schedule strategic rock identification and decomposition workshop | Weeks 4-6 | Product Leadership |\
| 5 | **Design Tool Onboarding:** Figma Dev Mode setup; Relume training; CodeSpring integration | Weeks 2-3 | Design Lead + Tech Lead |\
| 6 | **Pilot Integration:** First epic using full design-to-code tool chain | Weeks 6-8 | Pilot Team |\
\
> **Long-term Commitment:** This is not a one-time transformation but a continuous journey of improvement. The Big Picture provides context and alignment, but the Ministry's teams own the practices\'97inspecting and adapting at every level to ensure that agility serves the mission of public service and **civic engagement**.\
\
